Anonymous Sun 29 Sep 2024 07:35:40 No.69559917 Report
Quoted By: >>69560037
>>69559816
Do they have self-rising cornmeal in stores near you? If not, it's more or less a 15:1 mix by volume of coarse yellow cornmeal and baking powder. If you don't live in the southeastern US it may not be available pre-mixed, but it's simple enough to sift them together before use. Hot dogs with no chicken would probably be a big improvement on the premade cheap store corndogs.

Restaurants used to use peanut oil but so many people are allergic to peanuts that they have switched to substitutes. A lot of restaurant deep fryers are filled with a cottonseed oil blend these days, mainly because it's cheap and has a high smoke point.
